SLPS College & Career Readiness Advisory Council

The Advisory Council ensures Saint Louis Public Schools stay aligned with current industry practices, emerging techniques, and evolving technologies while championing the training, resources, and professional development educators need. Council members also collaborate to expand learning experiences through fundraising for field trips, equipment, programming, and other opportunities.

Dr. Harvey R. Fields

Founding Dean, College of STEM

Harris-Stowe State University

Dr. Harvey R. Fields is the inaugural dean of Harris-Stowe’s College of STEM, appointed in 2023 after nearly two decades in student success leadership at Washington University in St. Louis, where he served as associate dean and site director for the Missouri Louis Stokes Alliance for Minority Participation and was recognized with the Gloria W. White Distinguished Service Award. His mandate at Harris-Stowe is to build programs and partnerships that expand access to high-demand STEM fields at Missouri’s only public HBCU.

Community impact. Fields’ work has focused on broadening participation in STEM through Missouri Louis Stokes Alliance for Minority Participation partnerships, including convenings that link Harris-Stowe students with federal science agencies and research ecosystems in St. Louis.

Rodrick Glass

Executive Vice President, Sales

Creative Realities, Inc.

Rodrick Glass is executive vice president for sales and business development at Creative Realities, a digital signage and retail media solutions firm, with prior experience founding and leading Allure Fusion Media. He contributes thought leadership on technology-enabled customer experience for quick-service and retail clients and has written and spoken for CRI on data-driven menu boards and personalization.

Community impact. Glass supports higher-education engagement through service on Purdue University’s Student Life Advisory Council, mentoring students on leadership and industry pathways.

Dr. Reggie Hill

Vice Chancellor for Strategic Enrollment and Career Advancement

University of Missouri-Saint Louis

Reggie Hill leads UMSL’s strategic enrollment and workforce integration portfolio, promoted from associate vice chancellor after joining the university in 2021. His responsibilities include recruitment, retention, student support services, and partnerships that align enrollment strategy with regional labor-market needs.

Community impact. Hill’s office advances inclusive access to higher education in the St. Louis region, and he serves in regional leadership networks to connect UMSL’s academic strengths with employer demand and civic priorities.

R. Brent Joy, MSACS, MBA

Senior AI Solution Engineer, Microsoft (AI Business Solutions and AI Workforce)

Microsoft

R. Brent Joy is a St. Louis based Senior AI Solution Engineer at Microsoft whose portfolio centers on AI Business Solutions and AI Workforce. Public materials indicate that his current remit involves architecting enterprise AI solutions and supporting adoption through customer-facing demonstrations, proofs of concept, and enablement aligned to the Microsoft 365 Copilot and Copilot Studio ecosystem.

Community impact. Joy’s practitioner outreach emphasizes practical AI upskilling for organizations, reflected in his public sharing of Microsoft Digital adoption case studies and webinar resources on Copilot deployment and prompting practices. His workforce orientation aligns with Microsoft’s broader initiatives to develop AI skills at scale and to engage labor partners on worker-centered adoption.

Tina Lindstrom

Head of Oil Derivatives Trading, North America

Marex

Tina Lindstrom leads North American oil derivatives trading at Marex and has more than twenty years of derivatives experience spanning equity index options, agricultural commodities, and energy markets. Public interviews profile her as a senior volatility portfolio manager and market maker who has built teams and initiatives in energy options, with prior roles at proprietary trading and market-making firms.

Community impact. Lindstrom serves with All Hands and Hearts, where she chairs development and supports disaster-relief rebuilding and education projects that mobilize volunteers and corporate partners.

Perry Stuckey

Former Senior Vice President and Chief Human Resources Officer

Eastman Chemical Company

Perry Stuckey served as senior vice president and CHRO of Eastman Chemical, overseeing global human capital strategy through periods of portfolio change and international expansion. He was recognized as a Fellow of the National Academy of Human Resources, reflecting career-long contributions to the HR profession.

Community impact. Eastman’s public materials credit Stuckey with advancing inclusion, leadership development, and community engagement initiatives tied to the company’s operations and workforce footprint.

Rose Kirk

Former Senior Vice President and Chief Corporate Social Responsibility Officer; Former President, Verizon Foundation

Verizon

Rose Kirk led Verizon’s global CSR and served as president of the Verizon Foundation, where she built flagship programs including Verizon Innovative Learning that scale access to technology and STEM opportunities. In public remarks and profiles she is cited for aligning corporate investments with measurable educational outcomes and digital inclusion.

Community impact. Verizon Innovative Learning Schools reached hundreds of thousands of students and tens of thousands of teachers with 1:1 devices and professional learning, and Verizon reports more than 7 million learners reached across VIL programs since inception.

Jenn Stein

Vice President, Innovation and Workforce Strategies

Kaptivate

Jenn Stein is vice president for innovation and workforce strategies at Kaptivate, with more than twenty years of program design and evaluation experience. Her publications for Kaptivate focus on youth work-based learning, internship pipelines, and communications infrastructure for workforce systems.

Community impact. Stein’s public writing and outreach foreground high school and CTE pathways, including work-based learning initiatives that expand paid internships and early exposure to in-demand careers.

Brian Smith

Trader

Old Mission Capital LLC

Brian C. Smith is a registered broker employed by Old Mission Capital LLC, a Chicago-based market maker specializing in complex ETF and options products, with prior registration at affiliated trading entities. FINRA BrokerCheck confirms his active registration and exam history.

Community impact. Market-making firms such as Old Mission provide liquidity and price discovery that underpin investor access to diversified ETFs, an ecosystem contribution recognized in industry profiles of the firm.

Dan Lester Sr.

Vice President of Field Culture and Inclusion

Clayco

Dan Lester has spent over a decade shaping careers in the construction industry. As Vice President of Field Culture and Inclusion at Clayco, Lester focuses on retention, mentorship, and creating conditions for workforce success. His approach blends data-driven decision-making with a deep respect for the human side of construction.

Community impact. Lester leads strategic initiatives that strengthen workplace culture and develop entry-level pathways into construction trades, ensuring that innovation serves both the project and the people behind it.
